    "description": "Imagine a world where the .NET developer can create and compile code that will run on multiple .NET platforms. The same code runs on WP, WPF, SL, XBox, and Windows Store apps. You can, and there are a few options available to you, such as linked files and the little hidden gem in Visual Studio 2012 (available also for Visual Studio 2010) called Portable Class Libraries.",
